      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SOHO HUDSON (1) finished seventh at Kilmore on April 2 then turned things around last time, making up plenty of ground in a sustained run only to find a couple better over 1690m at Maryborough. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Must raise the bar but he has the ability to test this field. GALAXY LASS (9) has been competitive of late and kept the ball rolling last time when 4 metres from the winner in fourth over 2240m at Melton. This is a nice drop in grade so she is in the right race to find the winners' list. HELLOVATIME (7) has to come into calculations on the back of some strong recent form, most recently when second at Shepparton over 2190m. Must be included. JUST AS WELL NZ (8) is the best of the rest after finishing sixth over 1650m at Bendigo last time out.",
